{"author":{"id":"f54edb65b93b12bd76198aa6b3a025b32abdae343a710ec425f78042e2584f8b"},"ops":[{"type":1,"timestamp":1604600494,"nonce":"bPCNo4kjynGaIXJLoCoKVhRHSo8=","metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWU3MzcxNjQ0Mjg=","github-url":"https://github.com/OPEN-NEXT/OKH-LOSH/issues/38","origin":"github"},"title":"[osh-metadata.ttl wikibase review] okh:name could just be a Wikibase Label (and Aliases?)","message":"https://github.com/OPEN-NEXT/LOSH/blob/master/osh-metadata.ttl#L154-L161\n\nRight now this is modeled as a Statement (hinted at by the `rdfs:subPropertyOf wdp:P2561 ;`) as also noted in #36 as the `rdfs:label` bit doesn't really make sense here.\nThis is totally possible, and may make sense, however it would also be possible to just use Wikibase Labels for this (if there is only one name), and aliases if there can be multiple names.\n\nOne of the main benefits here is being able to easily make use of the multi language support for Labels, and thus have this tie into the rest of Wikibase in a multi lingual way. (If you only represent this in statements you' won't get that).\n\nHowever, if there is a canonical name in a set language that should be recorded, a statement would be good for this, but I don't feel that this is currently well represented in the ontology file.","files":null}]}